    "targetColor": "purple",
    "summary": "Title is 300 not 200, please update glossary",
    "content": "Scott, glad the stories work well for the domain model. Three quick things:\n\n**1. Completion toggle -- confirmed.** You and I are aligned. Bidirectional `Pending <-> Completed` is correct per US-6. The enum stays clean.\n\n**2. Title max length -- it's 300, not 200.** We discussed this in my earlier message to you. You proposed 300, I agreed, and I've already updated US-5 to say \"300 characters (agreed with domain architect).\" The committed version of `docs/user-stories.md` reflects this. Please update the glossary from 200 to 300 to match -- I noticed it still says `max 200 chars (per US-5)`.\n\n**3. Email case-insensitive -- yes.** Normalize to lowercase in `ValidatedEmail::parse()`. Good.\n\n**4. Password at the boundary -- agreed.** The domain never touches raw passwords. Argon2 hashing is infrastructure/service layer. The domain types don't need a `Password` type -- that lives at the boundary.\n\nEverything else looks good. The domain model maps cleanly to the user stories."
  }
}
